pr_body:
Settings changes - 
"custom_headers": {"X-API-VERSION": "Version 1.1.0"}

It will send a custom header to API like HTTP_X_API_VERSION which is helpful in defining API versions.

@eric-haibin-lin thanks for resolving conflicts!
@reminisce @piiswrong @bhavinthaker
See original PR + code review: https://github.com/eric-haibin-lin/mxnet/pull/173

It's convenient to define custom pageblocks' create_from_dict method
as passing in the complete dictionary as kwargs on creation. e.g.:

```python
@classmethod
def create_from_dict(cls, d):
    return cls.objects.create(**d)
```

In order for this to work, the basic keys that the dictionary
will contain: `block_type`, `label`, and `css_extra` need to be
removed before calling the custom pageblock's create_from_dict hook.

@vitaly-krugl please review

cc @subutai @mrcslws 

